Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.93,0:01:43.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,Junio
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.62,0:01:45.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(479,520)}Koyomi Sand
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.98,0:01:54.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,Buenos días Fatigaragi.{Good morning, Tiredragi-san.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.52,0:01:55.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,Fatigaragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.76,0:01:56.96,HnF,,0,0,0,,Espera un momento, Hachikuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.42,0:02:02.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,No hables de manera que parezca que estás harta de mí.{Don’t call out to me with that weariness that makes it look like you're fed up with talking to me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:03.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,Mi nombre es Araragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.20,0:02:05.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo siento, me mordí la lengua.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.74,0:02:07.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, fue a propósito.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.62,0:02:08.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,Me dormí la lengua.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.53,0:02:10.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No fue a propósito?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.10,0:02:12.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,Así que... ¿A dónde vas a ir hoy?{So, Araragi-san where are you headed to today?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.88,0:02:15.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como puedes ver, ahora estoy de camino a clase.  {As you can see, I’m off to school now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.44,0:02:17.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Te lo dije el otro día, ¿no?{I told you the other day, didn’t I?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.44,0:02:21.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,He pasado de ser un delincuente estúpido\N a un estudiante que atiende en clase. {He cambiado los papeles de un delincuente estúpido, a un estudiante que está atento en clase.}{I’ve changed roles from a stupid delinquent into a student who’s sincere about his work.}{Viva la traducción libre!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.97,0:02:23.84,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por lo que ahora voy a clase.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.86,0:02:28.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,De todas maneras, incluso la gente que no atiende va a clase también.{Although, even insincere students go to school, too.}{V.2}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.41,0:02:30.73,HnF,,0,0,0,,Oye, Hachikuji...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.73,0:02:33.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hay algo que tengo que decirte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.46,0:02:34.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿De qué se trata?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.53,0:02:37.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,Oshino... Oshino Meme...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.66,0:02:42.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ese viejo especialista que te ayudó...\N se fue de la ciudad.{That old specialist guy that helped you out... he left town.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.62,0:02:45.84,HnF,,0,0,0,,Parece que se fue sin avisar, ¿no?{Bueno, eso ha sido bastante repentino, ¿no?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.44,0:02:51.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ya que nunca lo conociste en persona, puede que esto no te interese...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:55.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,{Aunque pueda darte igual}De todas formas, creo que debo contártelo\N por si acaso.{Well, though you aren't indifferent to it, but I thought I should tell you just in case.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.29,0:03:01.25,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, Araragi. ¿Qué pasó con 'eso' al final?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.25,0:03:03.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿'Eso'? ¿a qué te refieres?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.97,0:03:07.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como dije, me refiero a 'eso'.{Like I said. It's this, you see, this.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.08,0:03:12.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces sería mejor si dijera esto, Araragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.44,0:03:15.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tu impago de los 5 millones de yenes. Buen trabajo.{Your failure to pay the 5 million yen is much appreciated.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:17.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡No los dejé sin pagar!{I didn’t fail to pay it!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.68,0:03:21.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,Mira Hachikuji, yo soy el tipo de persona que devuelve el dinero que le han prestado.{Look, Hachikuji. I’m the kind of guy that returns money he borrows.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.36,0:03:24.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,He pagado completamente lo que le debía a Oshino.{I’ve properly repaid my debt to Oshino.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.52,0:03:27.83,HnF,,0,0,0,,Con eso liquidado, estoy completamente libre de deudas.{With that over with, I’m completely debt-free and clean.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:29.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Estás seguro?{Is that so?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.26,0:03:31.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,Estoy un poco decepcionada con eso.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:33.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.90,0:03:36.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No te lo dije el otro día?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.52,0:03:37.64,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿El otro día?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.88,0:03:42.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cuando tú estabas siendo perseguido por esa discípula tuya{When you were being stalked by that very fast junior of yours,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.16,0:03:45.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,me dijiste que le debías mucho dinero a Oshino,{You were asking me, I owe a huge amount of money to Oshino-san}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:47.65,HnF,,0,0,0,,y que qué deberías hacer... o algo así.{and what should I do, or something like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.12,0:03:52.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,No dijiste algo como que incluso si no tenías dinero en efectivo,{Didn’t you say something like, even if you didn’t have any hard cash,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.52,0:03:58.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,si llegase a haber una extraña historia sobre excentricidades, ¿serías capaz de pagar la deuda?{If there was an unusual story about an oddity, you’d be able to turn it into cash, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.60,0:04:00.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Dije todo eso?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.50,0:04:03.07,HnF,,0,0,0,,De todas maneras, Araragi,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.07,0:04:08.43,HnF,,0,0,0,,desde entonces he estado pensando si podría ayudar de alguna forma.{Since then, I was wondering if I could be of any help to Araragi-san.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.43,0:04:15.31,HnF,,0,0,0,,Durante mis paseos, he estado buscando historias de excentricidades como esas.{So during my walks, I’ve been looking for stories like those 'Oddity stories’, or even 'ghost stories’.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.30,0:04:20.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Realmente estabas haciendo eso por mí?{Were you really doing that for me?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.05,0:04:26.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y ahora se acaba de arruinar mi plan de venderte, a un gran precio, esta historia que he encontrado.{Ahora mi plan de venderte esta historia que he encontrado por un gran precio, fue arruinado.}{Now my scheme to sell this story I managed to find to Araragi-san for a high price is ruined.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.52,0:04:28.19,HnF,,0,0,0,,!¿Una historia... por un gran precio?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.19,0:04:29.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh, no me lo ibas a dar simplemente?{Eh, you weren’t going to give it to me?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.81,0:04:30.85,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Por supuesto que no!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.49,0:04:37.51,HnF,,0,0,0,,Araragi, ahora que ya no sirve,{estamos así,} no voy a pedir tanto como 5 millones, pero cómpramela por favor.{Araragi-san. Now that it’s like this. I won’t go as high as five million yen, so please buy it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.51,0:04:39.61,HnF,,0,0,0,,Va a ser una ganga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.61,0:04:44.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Y por cuanto dinero estás intentando venderla, Hachikuji?{Incidentally, how much were you aiming to sell it for, Hachikuji?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.34,0:04:46.12,HnF,,0,0,0,,Unos cinco yenes estará bien.{Around fifty yen is fine.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.12,0:04:47.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Qué barato!{That’s cheap!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.16,0:04:50.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,Realmente la historia solo valía eso.{Para empezar, la historia solo valía eso desde el principio. }{Well, you see, this story was worth only that much from the beginning.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.87,0:04:54.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡¿Estabas planeando venderle a tu amigo una historia que solo valía cinco yenes, por 5 millones?!{Were you planning on selling a story worth only fifty yen to your friend for five million yen?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.96,0:04:59.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, ¿qué tipo de historia es?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.10,0:05:02.37,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí. Eh... Una historia sobre arena.{Yes. Eh, so it’s a story about sand.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.37,0:05:03.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Arena?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:04.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,Koyomi Sand
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.15,0:05:17.28,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Cómo decirlo... Aquello se parecía al rostro de un demonio.{How should I put it, it looked like the expression of a demon.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.28,0:05:18.94,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Un cuadro espeluznante.{A bloodcurdling drawing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:23.00,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Como si la propia arena fuese una excentricidad.{As if the sand itself was almost like an oddity.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.00,0:05:30.94,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Hachikuji estaba buscando historias sobrenaturales que venderme.{Because Hachikuji was going around looking for some strange or suspicious phenomenon to try and sell to me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.94,0:05:37.06,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Tal vez por eso, ella pudo haber visto en un arenero normal, algo misterioso.{ It's possible she might have gone and seen the originally normal sandbox as something more mysterious.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.06,0:05:44.62,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Siendo así, ¿cómo es posible ver la misma expresión sobre la arena dos días distintos?{So was it possible to see the same 'demon expression’ on different days?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.62,0:05:51.14,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Dicho de otra forma, no importa como movieses o mezclases la arena en ese arenal,{In other words, no matter how it was changed or mixed around, the sand in this sandbox,}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.14,0:05:54.30,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,siempre volvía a la forma de un demonio.{always returned to a demon’s shape.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.30,0:05:56.30,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Una extravagancia recurrente.{A recurring bizarreness}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:06:00.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como si la arena tuviese voluntad propia.{As if the sand had a will of its own.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.16,0:06:06.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, pensándolo tranquilamente,\N tiene que ser alguien jugando con ella.{ Well, if thinking about it normally, it has to be just somebody playing around.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:14.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,Esto es arena normal después de todo.{This is just regular sand.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.82,0:06:25.12,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Pensé que si jugaba con ella como lo haría un niño,\N tal vez encontrase una respuesta...{Maybe if I played in the same way a kid would play in this sandbox, there would be some kind of response.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.98,0:06:31.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si fuese una broma, se trataría de una de mal gusto.{Si es una broma, no es una muy elogiable.}{If it’s a prank, it might not be something as impressive.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.56,0:06:36.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,De cualquier manera, no parece que haya ninguna necesidad de que me involucre.{Either way, it doesn’t seem like there’s any need for me to get involved.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.94,0:06:43.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si fuese una excentricidad, no se mostraría tan fácilmente. Pero si fuese el trabajo de un humano...{If it’s an oddity, it’s not going to show itself so easily but it could also be the work of a human.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.20,0:06:48.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Araragi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.36,0:06:51.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,Siento llamar a estas horas, pero hay algo que me intriga. ¿Es un buen momento?{Sorry for calling at such a time but there was something that I was curious about. Is it a good time?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.74,0:06:54.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Está bien, ¿qué pasa?{Lo es, ¿por qué?}{It’s all right, but-}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.26,0:06:58.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hace un momento, he recibido el informe periódico de Senjougahara.{A little while ago, I received a periodical report from Senjougahara-san.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.08,0:07:00.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡¿Informe periódico?! ¡¿Que quiere decir eso?!{Periodical report?! What do you mean by that?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.48,0:07:03.61,HnF,,0,0,0,,En ese momento me enteré de la noticia.{Entonces me llegó la noticia.}{So during that time, I just happened to hear about it,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.61,0:07:11.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,Escuché que ibas a inspeccionar \Nel arenero del parque que tienes cerca.{But Araragi-kun, I heard that you were going to investigate some sand in a park on your way back.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.87,0:07:14.43,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Lo has hecho ya?{Are you done with that already?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.43,0:07:18.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pensé que podría esperar a que acabases para llamarte.{Pensé que podía esperar a llamarte una vez que hubieses acabado.}{ I thought I’d try and time it so that I would call you once you were done.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.64,0:07:21.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Mal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.66,0:07:23.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Acaso eres un inútil, Araragi?{Isn’t this a bit hopeless, Araragi-kun?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:27.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,Esperaba que ya pudieses haberlo resuelto más o menos,{I had hoped that you would have resolved everything neatly,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.48,0:07:31.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,pensaba hacer más bien una recapitulación.{and I was planning on more of a follow-up report.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.21,0:07:31.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,Informe de investigación{Report of investigation}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.92,0:07:32.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,Recapitulación
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.45,0:07:35.01,HnF,,0,0,0,,Una recapitulación...{A follow-up report.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:39.98,HnF,,0,0,0,,Araragi, has olvidado algo importante, deberías abrir más tu perspectiva.{Araragi-kun, you’ve forgotten something important. You’re just looking at it too rigidly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.98,0:07:41.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Perspectiva?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.30,0:07:45.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,"El arenero en cuestión es obra de una excentricidad o de un fenómeno artificial."{Whether the sandbox in question is the work of an oddity, or an artificial phenomenon.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.90,0:07:49.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,Decir que es una de dos opciones sin más,\N es tener falta de perspectiva.{Saying that it has to be one of the two is too rigid. Isn’t it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:52.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, supongo que sí.{Well, I suppose it is.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:55.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Hay más posibilidades?{Are there other possibilities?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:59.84,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hay más posibilidades. Una más, de hecho.{There are other possibilities. A third possibility.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.84,0:08:04.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Así que sí hay, ¿eh?\N Como era de esperarse, lo sabes todo.{Heh, so there is something like that.\NYou really know everything, don’t you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.56,0:08:08.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,No lo sé todo. Solo sé lo que sé.{I don’t know everything. I just know what I know.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:09.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,La tercera posibilidad...{The third option.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.92,0:08:15.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si no es obra de una excentricidad ni de un humano...{If it’s neither the work of an oddity nor an artificial phenomenon, then it would be...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.88,0:08:21.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pensándolo detenidamente \Nusando el proceso de eliminación...{descartando las otras opciones...}{Um, well, thinking about it properly If I use process of elimination,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.46,0:08:25.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,Solo puedo pensar en un fenómeno natural.{ then the only thing I can think of is it being a natural phenomenon.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.34,0:08:29.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Eso es! al final lo has entendido, Araragi.{That’s right, so you do understand, Araragi-kun!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.36,0:08:34.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero fenómeno natural... no hay forma de que-{But a natural phenomenon, there’s no way that's-}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.08,0:08:39.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,Escucha Araragi, los fenómenos naturales no se limitan al viento y la lluvia.{Listen Araragi-kun. Natural phenomena aren't only just wind and rain.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.54,0:08:46.32,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y ahora el epílogo, o mejor, la conclusión.{And now for the epilogue, or rather, the punch line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.32,0:08:48.65,HnF,,0,0,0,,Oye, Araragi.{Hey, Araragi-kun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.65,0:08:55.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cuando investigaste el arenero, solo viste la arena, ¿no?{When you investigated the sandbox, you only looked at the sand, didn’t you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.24,0:08:59.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero el arenero solo es eso, cuando incluyes el contenedor.{But the sandbox is only a sandbox when you include the container.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:03.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por eso, Araragi, si vas a investigar el arenero,{ That’s why, Araragi-kun, if you’re going to investigate the 'sandbox’,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.80,0:09:08.15,HnF,,0,0,0,,también deberías investigar el contenedor, o no lo habrás investigado adecuadamente.{you have to investigate the container as well, or you wouldn’t have investigated it properly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:11.61,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cuando piensas en la arena, normalmente no es pesada.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.61,0:09:14.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque depende de las condiciones, puede serlo.{When you think of sand, it’s usually weighty. As long as there’s nothing unusual, that is.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.77,0:09:19.66,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,No había necesidad de pensarlo más.{There was no need to think anymore.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.66,0:09:22.62,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,El fondo del contenedor tenía una fisura,{Since the bottom of the container of the 'sandbox’ had fissured,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:28.22,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,probablemente por deterioro, y por el peso de la arena,{likely due to deterioration and since it had fissured together with the weight of the sand,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.22,0:09:32.68,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,como Hanekawa sabía, la respuesta era que la arena se filtraba por ahí.{that Hanekawa had mentioned, the answer was that the sand settled down to form a shape like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.68,0:09:37.93,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y el hecho de que fuese la cara de un demonio es,\N como era de esperar, una coincidencia.{The fact that it was the form of a demon was, as expected, a coincidence.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:43.28,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Ahora mismo, solo es un fenómeno natural que causa un extraño diseño en la arena.{Right now, it was only a natural phenomenon that would cause a strange design.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.28,0:09:46.17,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Pero si la fisura sigue extendiéndose,{But if the fissures of the container continued to get bigger,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.17,0:09:50.86,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,el fondo se partirá en trozos, la humedad se mezclará con la arena,{the floor would soon break into pieces and the dirt would mix with the sand,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.86,0:09:54.03,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,lo que podría causar arenas movedizas, o una licuefacción.{which could make it possible for quicksand or liquefaction to occur.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:09:59.13,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Esa sería lo peor que podría pasar.{That was the worst possible circumstance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.13,0:10:03.53,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y jugar en un contenedor roto\N puede ser muy peligroso.{And playing inside a fissured container was plenty dangerous.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.53,0:10:05.95,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Como una carrera contra el tiempo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.95,0:10:08.88,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Por eso Hanekawa se enfadó conmigo.{That’s why Hanekawa got angry with me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.36,0:10:13.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,De momento, debería llamar a la compañía que administra el parque.{For the time being I should call the company that manages the park.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:18.25,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,El que más miedo da, pero el más pacífico al final,{The scarier one, and the one that wasn’t peaceful at all,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.25,0:10:20.37,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,no era ni una excentricidad ni una persona,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.37,0:10:22.45,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,sino la naturaleza.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.21,0:10:27.41,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Tan aterradora como una excentricidad, tan aterradora como un humano.
